      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/2/19",
      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لَهُ اَلرَّجُلُ يَكُونُ لِي عَلَيْهِ حَقٌّ فَيَجْحَدُنِيهِ ثُمَّ يَسْتَوْدِعُنِي مَالاً أَ لِي أَنْ آخُذَ مَالِي عِنْدَهُ قَالَ \"لاَ هَذِهِ اَلْخِيَانَةُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3697 - Mu'awiyah ibn Ammar narrated from Abu Abdillah (as) who said:\nI said to him, \"A man owes me a right but denies it, and then he entrusts me with some money. Is it permissible for me to take my due from it?\"\nImam (as) said: \"No, that would be betrayal.\""
        ]
      }
    },
